Image Generation Prompt: Canvas tote bag wall hanging, bohemian style, macrame
Steps:
```html
  • Step 1: Gather materials: One canvas tote bag, yarn scraps (preferably in black, off-white, and beige), a crochet hook.
  • Step 2: Create the fringe: Cut numerous strands of yarn to create the fringe, ensuring sufficient length to hang below the tote bag.
  • Step 3: Attach the fringe: Securely attach the fringe to the bottom edge of the tote bag. You might use a crochet chain stitch to attach them evenly or simply knot them in place.
  • Step 4: Crochet the design: Using the yarn scraps, crochet a geometric design using black and off-white yarn, creating a central square pattern.
  • Step 5: Attach the design: Carefully attach the crocheted design to the center of the tote bag, using crochet stitches or strong fabric glue.
  • Step 6: Add tassels: Create small tassels from the yarn scraps and attach them on the four corners of the crocheted square to finish the design.
```
